Package chess

Class Board

java.lang.Object
chess.Board
public class Board
extends java.lang.Object
This class handles all moves that are done in the game as well as handles "draws", "resigns", "checks", and "checkmates". This class also contains the "Chess Board", which contains all the current pieces that are currently in play, and prints the board as well.
Author:
Savan Patel, Naveenan Yogeswaran

    • makeMove

      public boolean makeMove​(char color, java.lang.String colorFullName, java.lang.String opponent, java.util.Scanner scan)
      Handles each player's turn. This method also checks for bad input, draws, resigns, resets en passant, prints the winner of the game, and calls promotion for Pawns when necessary.
      Parameters:
      color - Color of the player who's turn it is ('w' or 'b').
      colorFullName - Full name of the color ('White' or 'Black').
      opponent - Full name of the color of the opponent ('White' or 'Black').
      scan - Scanner object that takes in input from user.
      Returns:
      True if the game is still continuing, False if the game ended (either through draw, resign, checkmate, etc.)

    • promote

      public void promote​(int file, int rank, char type, char color)
      This method will promote the Pawn, at the given location, into a new Piece.
      Parameters:
      file - Column index of the Pawn to be promoted.
      rank - Row index of the Pawn to be promoted.
      type - The new type that the Pawn should be promoted to.
      color - The color of the Pawn that is to be promoted.

    • check

      public boolean check​(char color)
      This method checks the King of the given color. This method checks the King's horizontal and vertical for Rooks and Queens, diagonals for Bishops and Queens, spots for Pawns, spots for Knights, and it's immediate surrounding for opposing King.
      Parameters:
      color - Color of the King that is being checked.
      Returns:
      True if the King is not in check, False if King is in check.

    • checkmate

      public boolean checkmate​(char color)
      Checks to see if there are any possible ways for the King to escape check.
      Parameters:
      color - Color of the King that is being checked.
      Returns:
      True if King is in checkmate, False if King is not in checkmate
